{{Otheruses|New Plympto resistance}}
{{Quote|You may have heard of the resistance on New Plympto, in the Corellian sector. Numa is a leader of that resistance.|Lando Calrissian|<ref name="Rebirth">''[[The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory II: Rebirth]]''</ref>}}
The '''New Plympto resistance''' was the [[Nosaurian/Legends|Nosaurian]] resistance movement on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[New Plympto/Legends|New Plympto]] against the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] during [[Yuuzhan Vong War|their invasion]] of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. It was led by [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Numa Rar|Numa]] and [[Alema Rar]]; the [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] sisters only went into public one at a time, with their [[Lekku/Legends|lekku]] hidden, causing the Yuuzhan Vong to believe they were a single [[Human/Legends|Human]] woman. [[Kyp's Dozen]], a [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] ran supplies for them.

In [[27 ABY/Legends|27 ABY]], the Yuuzhan Vong tired of the resistance and unleashed a [[Virus (disambiguation)|virus]] onto the world, instantly [[Death/Legends|killing]] seven million of the planet's fifteen million inhabitants. The Rar sisters escaped with several thousand refugees.

